  "校验函数=判断+反馈": "A validator = judge + feedback",
  "一个好的校验函数做两件事:对内告诉调用方「这个值行不行」(用返回值 true/false),对外告诉用户「哪里错了」(把文字写进页面)。把这两件事放进同一个函数,调用处就能既拿到布尔结果做决策,又自动给用户看到提示。判断顺序从「最该先拦」的开始:先查空,再查格式。": "A good validator does two things: it tells the caller whether the value is acceptable (via a true/false return), and it tells the user what went wrong (by writing text into the page). Keeping both in one function lets the caller get a boolean to decide on while the user automatically sees the hint. Order checks from the one most worth catching first: emptiness, then format.",
  "先拦空、再拦格式,通过则清错并返回 true": "Catch empty, then format; on pass clear the error and return true",
  "textContent 还是 innerHTML?": "textContent or innerHTML?",
  "显示一段纯文字提示时,永远用 textContent。它把内容当成普通文字塞进去,不会解析里面的标签。如果你用 innerHTML,而错误文案里碰巧带了用户输入的内容,就可能把 <script> 当真执行,这是经典的 XSS 漏洞。规则简单:展示文字用 textContent,只有在确实要插入受信任的 HTML 时才用 innerHTML。": "To show a plain text message, always use textContent. It inserts the content as ordinary text and never parses tags inside it. If you use innerHTML and the message happens to include user input, a <script> could actually run — the classic XSS hole. The rule is simple: show text with textContent, and reach for innerHTML only when you truly need to insert trusted HTML.",
  "同样一段字,两种属性结果完全不同": "Same string, two properties, very different results",
