  "拦住非法提交": "Block the invalid submit",
  "拦提交": "Block",
  "给 #form 监听 submit 事件,在回调里先 e.preventDefault() 阻止默认跳转,再调用 validateEmail;只有校验通过才打印「提交成功」。": "Listen for submit on #form; in the handler call e.preventDefault() first to stop the navigation, then run validateEmail, and only log 'submitted' when it passes.",
  "监听用 form.addEventListener(\"submit\", (e) => { ... }),事件名是 submit,挂在 form 上,不是挂在按钮的 click 上。": "Listen with form.addEventListener(\"submit\", (e) => { ... }); the event is submit on the form, not click on the button.",
  "回调第一行就写 e.preventDefault()。它阻止浏览器默认的「提交并跳转/刷新」,让页面停在原地由你处理。": "Make e.preventDefault() the first line of the handler. It stops the browser's default 'submit and navigate/reload', keeping the page put so you handle it.",
  "用 submit 而不是按钮 click,是因为回车键也会触发 submit——挂 click 会漏掉键盘提交的用户。": "Use submit, not the button's click, because pressing Enter also fires submit — hooking click would miss keyboard submitters.",
  "监听 form 的 submit 事件": "Listen for the form's submit event",
  "写 form.addEventListener(\"submit\", ...)。": "Write form.addEventListener(\"submit\", ...).",
  "调用 preventDefault 阻止默认提交": "Call preventDefault to stop default submit",
  "在回调里写 e.preventDefault();。": "Write e.preventDefault(); inside the handler.",
  "校验通过才走成功分支": "Reach success only when validation passes",
  "用 if (validateEmail(...)) 包住成功逻辑,只有 true 才执行。": "Wrap the success path in if (validateEmail(...)) so only true runs it.",
  "默认提交是你的对手": "The default submit is your adversary",
  "<form> 天生就会在提交时让浏览器整页刷新或跳转到 action 地址,这是它在没有 JS 的年代的工作方式。但现在你想用 JS 校验,这个默认行为会在你校验之前就把页面带走。所以监听 submit 的第一件事永远是 e.preventDefault()——先把控制权抢过来,确认数据没问题再决定下一步。": "A <form> natively makes the browser reload the whole page or navigate to its action URL on submit — how it worked before JS existed. But now that you want to validate in JS, that default whisks the page away before you ever check. So the first thing a submit handler does is e.preventDefault() — seize control first, confirm the data is fine, then decide what happens next.",
  "preventDefault 在前,校验决定是否放行": "preventDefault first; validation decides whether to proceed",
  "想在校验通过后再真正发请求,就在那个 if 里调 fetch(),而不是依赖浏览器默认提交。": "To actually send the request after passing, call fetch() inside that if rather than relying on the browser's default submit.",
  "为什么监听 submit 而不是 click": "Why submit and not click",
  "新手常把校验挂在提交按钮的 click 上,这会漏掉一类真实用户:在输入框里直接按回车的人。浏览器规定,在表单里按回车等同于点击提交按钮,它触发的是 form 的 submit 事件,而不一定经过你监听的那个 click。把逻辑挂在 submit 上,鼠标点击和键盘回车两条路都能覆盖到。": "Beginners often hook validation to the submit button's click, which misses a real group of users: those who press Enter inside a field. The browser treats Enter in a form as clicking submit, and it fires the form's submit event, not necessarily the click you listened to. Hook the logic on submit and you cover both mouse clicks and keyboard Enter.",
  "submit 同时覆盖点击与回车两种提交方式": "submit covers both click and Enter ways of submitting",
  "别把 preventDefault 写在校验之后——一旦中间有 return 或抛错,默认提交就漏出去了。第一行就拦。": "Do not put preventDefault after the checks — if a return or error happens between, the default submit leaks through. Block it on line one.",
  "整合成一个可用的注册表单": "Assemble a working sign-up form",
  "整合": "Combine",
  "实现 validateForm:邮箱要含 @、密码长度 >= 8,任一不过就把对应错误写进 #emailError 或 #pwError 并返回 false;两项都过才返回 true。在 submit 回调里 preventDefault 后只在 validateForm 为真时打印「注册成功」。": "Implement validateForm: the email must contain @ and the password length must be >= 8; for any failure write the matching error into #emailError or #pwError and return false; return true only when both pass. In the submit handler, after preventDefault, log 'registered' only when validateForm is true.",
  "用一个 let ok = true 当总开关。每个字段校验失败就 ok = false,但不要立刻 return——继续校验后面的字段,把所有错误一次性显示出来。": "Use a let ok = true as the master switch. Set ok = false on each failure but do not return immediately — keep validating later fields so every error shows at once.",
  "密码长度判断用 password.length < 8。注意 length 是字符数,空格也算,所以密码框通常不 trim。": "Check the password with password.length < 8. Remember length counts characters including spaces, so password fields are usually not trimmed.",
  "每个字段合法时也要清空它对应的错误(textContent = \"\"),让上次的提示消失;两个 #emailError 和 #pwError 各管各的。": "On a passing field, also clear its own error (textContent = \"\") so the previous hint disappears; #emailError and #pwError each manage their own.",
  "校验邮箱含 @": "Validate the email contains @",
  "用 email.includes(\"@\") 判断邮箱,失败时写 emailErr 并把 ok 置 false。": "Check email with email.includes(\"@\"); on failure set emailErr and ok = false.",
