  "分别写 #emailError 和 #pwError": "Write #emailError and #pwError separately",
  "两个字段各写各的错误元素:#emailError 和 #pwError。": "Each field writes its own error element: #emailError and #pwError.",
  "preventDefault 后按校验结果放行": "After preventDefault, gate on the result",
  "回调先 e.preventDefault(),再用 if (validateForm(...)) 包住成功打印。": "Call e.preventDefault() first, then guard the success log with if (validateForm(...)).",
  "多字段:别第一个错就退场": "Many fields: don't bail on the first error",
  "单字段时「一错就 return」没问题,但表单有多个字段时这样做体验很差:用户改好邮箱再提交,才被告知密码也不行,如此往返好几次。正确做法是用一个 ok 标志,把每个字段都走一遍,该报错的报错、该清空的清空,最后统一返回 ok。这样用户一次就能看到所有问题。": "With one field, 'return on first error' is fine, but with several fields it is a bad experience: the user fixes the email, resubmits, and only then learns the password is wrong too — back and forth several times. The right way is an ok flag: run through every field, set errors and clear passes as needed, and return ok at the end. Now the user sees all problems at once.",
  "逐字段累积错误,最后返回总结果": "Accumulate per-field errors, then return the overall result",
  "每个字段的「清空」分支同样重要——它让用户改对后,上一次的红字立刻消失。": "The 'clear' branch of each field matters just as much — it makes the previous red text vanish the moment the user fixes it.",
  "把三关串成一条提交流水线": "Wire the three skills into one submit pipeline",
  "这就是这个节点的完整形态:监听 submit → preventDefault 抢回控制 → 读出每个字段的 value → validateForm 逐字段判断并显示错误 → 只有全过才真正「提交」。读输入、显示错误、阻止无效提交,三个技能在这里合成一个真实可用的注册表单。把成功分支里的 console.log 换成 fetch(),它就是线上能跑的代码。": "This is the node's finished shape: listen for submit, preventDefault to seize control, read each field's value, let validateForm judge field by field and show errors, and only 'submit' for real when all pass. Reading input, showing errors, and blocking invalid submits combine here into a real, usable sign-up form. Swap the console.log in the success branch for fetch() and it is production-ready code.",
  "拦截、读值、校验、放行——完整的提交闭环": "Block, read, validate, proceed — the complete submit loop",
  "密码别 trim()——空格也是合法密码字符,trim 掉会悄悄改了用户的密码,登录时就对不上了。": "Do not trim() the password — spaces are valid password characters; trimming silently alters it and login will then fail to match.",
  "render 是状态的纯函数": "render is a pure function of state",
  "入口": "Entry",
  "写一个 render(state) 函数：只读 state、只返回一段 HTML 字符串，不碰 DOM、不改 state。": "Write render(state) that only reads state and returns an HTML string — touching no DOM and mutating no state.",
  "用反引号模板字符串：`<h1>计数：${state.count}</h1>`，把数据插进 HTML。": "Use a backtick template string: `<h1>计数：${state.count}</h1>` to interpolate data into HTML.",
  "render 里别写 document.querySelector 或赋值给 state，那会破坏「纯函数」这一前提。": "Don't call document.querySelector or assign to state inside render — that breaks the pure-function premise.",
